The paper deals with stochastic dynamic programming, which is a subfield of operations research and control theory. However, the paper also heavily relies on linear programming and approximation algorithms, which are core topics in computer science. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.OC (Optimization and Control), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
